Manchester United  beat Chelsea 1-0
to open their Champions League soccer quarterfinal, while
Barcelona routed Shakhtar Donetsk 5-1.  Wayne Rooney  scored the only goal in the 24th minute to
give Manchester United the win at Stamford Bridge in london.  Andres Iniesta, Dani Alves, Gerard Pique, Seydou Keita and
Xavi Hernandez scored to lead Barcelona, the favorite with U.K.
bookmakers to win Europeâ€™s top club competition, to the home
win.  Manchester United and Shakhtar will host the return matches
